
[1]exhaustion

   EXHAUST'ION, n. The act of drawing out or draining off; the act of
   emptying completely of the contents.

   1. The state of being exhausted or emptied; the state of being deprived
   of strength or spirits.

   2. In mathematics, a method of proving the equality of two magnitudes
   by a reductio ad absurdum, or showing that if one is supposed either
   greater or less than the other, there will arise a contradiction.
